README.md
     3→# Swarm (experimental, educational)
     5→> [!IMPORTANT]
     6→> Swarm is now replaced by the [OpenAI Agents SDK](https://github.com/openai/openai-agents-python), which is a production-ready evolution of Swarm. The Agents SDK features key improvements and will be actively maintained by the OpenAI team.
     7→>
     8→> We recommend migrating to the Agents SDK for all production use cases.
     9→
    10→## Install
    24→## Usage
    60→## Table of Contents
    72→# Overview
    74→Swarm focuses on making agent **coordination** and **execution** lightweight, highly controllable, and easily testable.
    75→
    76→It accomplishes this through two primitive abstractions: `Agent`s and **handoffs**. An `Agent` encompasses `instructions` and `tools`, and can at any point choose to hand off a conversation to another `Agent`.
    77→
    78→These primitives are powerful enough to express rich dynamics between tools and networks of agents, allowing you to build scalable, real-world solutions while avoiding a steep learning curve.
    79→
    80→> [!NOTE]
    81→> Swarm Agents are not related to Assistants in the Assistants API. They are named similarly for convenience, but are otherwise completely unrelated. Swarm is entirely powered by the Chat Completions API and is hence stateless between calls.
    82→
    83→## Why Swarm
    89→# Examples
    91→Check out `/examples` for inspiration! Learn more about each one in its README.
    92→
    93→- [`basic`](examples/basic): Simple examples of fundamentals like setup, function calling, handoffs, and context variables
    94→- [`triage_agent`](examples/triage_agent): Simple example of setting up a basic triage step to hand off to the right agent
    95→- [`weather_agent`](examples/weather_agent): Simple example of function calling
    96→- [`airline`](examples/airline): A multi-agent setup for handling different customer service requests in an airline context.
    97→- [`support_bot`](examples/support_bot): A customer service bot which includes a user interface agent and a help center agent with several tools
    98→- [`personal_shopper`](examples/personal_shopper): A personal shopping agent that can help with making sales and refunding orders
    99→
   100→# Documentation
   104→## Running Swarm
   114→### `client.run()`
   126→#### Arguments
   141→#### `Response` Fields
   149→## Agents
   155→## `Agent` Fields
   165→### Instructions
   197→## Functions
   229→### Handoffs and Updating Context Variables
   281→### Function Schemas
   321→## Streaming
   336→# Evaluations
   338→Evaluations are crucial to any project, and we encourage developers to bring their own eval suites to test the performance of their swarms. For reference, we have some examples for how to eval swarm in the `airline`, `weather_agent` and `triage_agent` quickstart examples. See the READMEs for more details.
   339→
   340→# Utils
   342→Use the `run_demo_loop` to test out your swarm! This will run a REPL on your command line. Supports streaming.
   343→
   344→```python
   345→from swarm.repl import run_demo_loop
   346→...
   347→run_demo_loop(agent, stream=True)
   348→```
   349→
